    <p>
      Because there is a downward trend in <xref ref="multiunitsVsOwnership">Figure</xref>
      <mdash/> counties with more units in multi-unit structures are associated with lower homeownership <mdash/> these variables are said to be
      <em>negatively associated</em>.
          <idx><h>negative association|textbf</h></idx>
      A<nbsp/><term>positive association</term>
      is shown in the relationship between the <c>median\ushh\usincome</c> and <c>pop\uschange</c> in <xref ref="pop_change_v_med_income">Figure</xref>,
      where counties with higher median household income tend to have higher rates of population growth.
    </p>
    <p>
      If two variables are not associated,
      then they are said to be <term>independent</term>.
      That is, two variables are independent if there is no evident relationship between the two.
    </p>
